{
  "name": "leios_cascading_vote_batches",
  "description": "The server offers EB1 (slot=100) then delivers 50 valid votes in five consecutive MsgLeiosVotes batches (voters 1-10, 11-20, 21-30, 31-40, 41-50). All votes are for the same EB hash from distinct voter IDs so every vote is independently legitimate. In the Leios spec votes accumulate per-EB across all incoming VT-Role-Action firings from different peers; no batch resets the running tally. A node that discards earlier batches when a new one arrives, or that only counts the most recent batch, would miscount the tally and either fail to form a certificate that should have quorum or fail to detect that quorum has been reached. A conforming node must persistently accumulate all 50 votes and reflect the correct running total after each batch.",
